Vendored from https://github.com/antirez/linenoise
Upstream commit: a473823d74b93eab2ba83480df16ed37617493f2

Local modification: a Ctrl-G hook (linenoiseSetEditorCallback) that hands the
current line to an external editor and replaces it with the result. Search for
"editorCallback" / "CTRL_G" to find the delta.

Local modification: linenoiseSetPromptStyle(ansi) wraps the prompt and edited
line in a host-supplied zero-width SGR sequence (reset with \033[0m after),
applied on both the initial paint and every refresh. The styled rows are filled
to the terminal edge with EL (\033[K) under the active background. Search for
"promptStyle".

Local modification: linenoiseSetTopInfo(text)/linenoiseSetBottomInfo(text)
reserve a single status row immediately above and below the prompt, styled like
the prompt bar (NULL removes the row, "" keeps it blank). They are folded into
the multi-line row/cursor accounting and the initial paint. Search for
"topInfo" / "bottomInfo" / "emitInfoRow".

Local modification: when the prompt is styled or has status rows,
linenoiseEditStop() erases the whole prompt block and clears any active SGR,
leaving the cursor where the block began (instead of just printing a newline),
so exit (e.g. Ctrl-D) leaves the terminal clean and the host can redraw from a
known position. Search for "linenoiseEditStop".
